"Necessary decisions following the assessment, and required follow-up. # ANNEX 12\n\n# IMPROVING WATER QUALITY IN A THERAPEUTIC FEEDING CENTRE\nBoth the quality and the quantity of the water supply must be adequate in a therapeutic feeding centre (TFC) in order to ensure appropriate care and feeding. The recommended amount of water is usually 30 l per patient and per day; 10 litres are the absolute minimum."